To avoid interference with aircraft naviga-
tion and communications systems, portable
telepnone and electronic devices which are re-
motely controlled are prohibited through out the
flight.
The following devices are permitted to be op-
erated by passenger after aircraft reaches safe al-
titude. Portable voice recorders, portable self pow-
ered computers, recording typewriters and word
processors, hand-held calculators and electronic
games, electric shavers, and CD players/
walkmans.
There are no restrictions on use of hearing aids
and heart pacemakers.
SEAT BELT
To fasten seat belt simply insert the buckle
and adjust the length, lower the belt on the
torso as much as possible, then tighten the belt.
For safety, please don't fasten seat belt around
waist and don't put pillow or blanket between belt
and body except on a child.
